snippet.textDisplay:
There are different types of 5G:
mmWave, mid-band, and low band.
T-Mobile has deployed it's low band 5g Nationwide last month. AT&T, Verizon, as well as T-Mobile, have deployed mmWave towers in a few cities. Sprint is the only provider to deploy mid-band 5g, which is a creme della creme between low band and mmWave (the reason why T-Mobile wants to merge with Sprint.)
